title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 – Oct 20 2022
itunes:title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 – Oct 20 2022
description:
Midterms look good for GOP. Buck says, "It feels like we're finally at a moment of national sanity, national healing." Dr. Oz pulls ahead of Fetterman. What will journos do with election going south for Dems? Whoopi Goldberg rips Meghan Markle. Clay says, "Meghan Markle is so tone-deaf that she managed to align this show with The View." Liz Truss out as UK PM after just 44 days. Biden claims Strategic Petroleum Reserve release isn't political, but everyone knows it is. Peter Doocy nails KJP on Dems wanting to end fossil fuels. MSNBC's Hayes says future of American democracy depends on gas prices. C&B explain what it really means when Dems say that.

Follow Clay & Buck on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/c/clayandbuck
